    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-09T05:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-09T05:30:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">745.45F/6–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in India</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donovan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-09T16:00:00+05:30"
                            >June 9, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>464. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 346, June 3. Both British and
                    American military attachés summoned to general headquarters yesterday afternoon
                    and informed by Chief of Staff Kalwant Singh that <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> now possesses conclusive evidence presence Pakistan battalion
                    in Kashmir west of Uri. Battalion identified as first 13 frontier force rifles.
                    Apparently Indian troops in latest advance west of Uri came in contact Pakistan
                    battalion which according Kalwant Singh retreated toward west.</p>
                <p>Kalwant Singh also said he “believes” there were two or three other Pakistan
                    battalions in Kashmir. It is as yet too soon determine what action <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> will take re this development. Department will
                    be kept informed.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 464; repeated Karachi 102. Department pass London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Donovan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
